cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

The paper deals with a deep learning architecture for multi-exposure fusion, which involves computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML) techniques. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of a no-reference quality metric as a loss function, which falls under the sub-category of multimedia (MM) and image processing. The paper proposes an unsupervised deep learning framework, which involves training a CNN architecture, and hence, falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (ML) and artificial intelligence (AI). Finally, the paper deals with generating artifact-free perceptually pleasing results, which involves graphics (GR) techniques.
